claim.claim-text:
1. A pressure gradient dosing system for a fluid supply system, comprising an additive delivery system having a fluid inlet and a fluid outlet, a flow passage including a portion extending from said inlet to said outlet, a first pressure zone along said flow passage communicating with said inlet, a second pressure zone along said flow passage communicating with outlet, said second pressure zone having a lower pressure than said first pressure zone, such that there is a pressure gradient between said first and second pressure zones, an additive reservoir responsive to said pressure gradient to release additive to said flow passage, wherein:
fluid flows from upstream to downstream along said flow passage, including from said inlet to said outlet;
said flow passage has a pressure reducer therealong creating said pressure gradient;
said additive reservoir has first and second ports, said first port communicating with said first pressure zone, said second port communicating with said second pressure zone;
said flow passage has first and second branches in parallel, said first branch being a main fluid flow branch, said second branch diverging from said main branch at said first pressure zone then passing through said additive reservoir then returning to and re-joining said main branch at said second pressure zone, said second branch flowing around and bypassing said pressure reducer;
said first and second branches diverge upstream of said pressure reducer.

2. The pressure gradient dosing system according to claim 1 wherein:
said pressure reducer comprises one or more flow restrictors;
said one or more flow restrictors have an upstream side communicating with each of said inlet, said first pressure zone, and said first port;
said one or more flow restrictors have a downstream side communicating with each of said outlet, said second pressure zone, and said second port.

3. The pressure gradient dosing system according to claim 2 wherein:
said one or more flow restrictors comprise one or more orifices along said flow passage creating said pressure gradient;
said one or more orifices have an upstream side communicating with each of said inlet, said first pressure zone, and said first port;
said one or more orifices have a downstream side communicating with each of said outlet, said second pressure zone, and said second port.

4. The pressure gradient dosing system according to claim 2 wherein:
said or more flow restrictors comprise a venturi along said flow passage creating said pressure gradient;
said venturi has an upstream side communicating with each of said inlet, said first pressure zone, and said first port;
said venturi has a downstream side communicating with each of said outlet, said second pressure zone, and said second port.

25. A pressure gradient dosing system for a fluid supply system, comprising an additive delivery system having a fluid inlet and a fluid outlet, a flow passage including a portion extending from said inlet to said outlet, a first pressure zone along said flow passage communicating with said inlet, a second pressure zone along said flow passage communicating with outlet, said second pressure zone having a lower pressure than said first pressure zone, such that there is a pressure gradient between said first and second pressure zones, an additive reservoir responsive to said pressure gradient to release additive to said flow passage,
wherein:
fluid flows from upstream to downstream along said flow passage, including from said inlet to said outlet;
said flow passage has a pressure reducer therealong creating said pressure gradient;
said additive reservoir has first and second ports, said first port communicating with said first pressure zone, said second port communicating with said second pressure zone;
said additive delivery system has a mounting plate for mounting in said fluid supply system, said additive reservoir being spaced from said mounting plate by a space therebetween, said pressure reducer being in said space,
and comprising a gasket between and engaging said mounting plate and said additive reservoir on distally opposite sides of said gasket, said gasket having a passage therethrough creating said pressure gradient thereacross.

26. A pressure gradient dosing system for a fluid supply system, comprising an additive delivery system having a fluid inlet and a fluid outlet, a flow passage including a portion extending from said inlet to said outlet, a first pressure zone along said flow passage communicating with said inlet, a second pressure zone along said flow passage communicating with outlet, said second pressure zone having a lower pressure than said first pressure zone, such that there is a pressure gradient between said first and second pressure zones, an additive reservoir responsive to said pressure gradient to release additive to said flow passage,
wherein:
fluid flows from upstream to downstream along said flow passage, including from said inlet to said outlet;
said flow passage has a pressure reducer therealong creating said pressure gradient;
said additive reservoir has first and second ports, said first port communicating with said first pressure zone, said second port communicating with said second pressure zone;
said additive delivery system has a mounting plate for mounting in said fluid supply system, said additive reservoir being spaced from said mounting plate by a space therebetween, said pressure reducer being in said space;
said additive reservoir has a plurality of tabs extending therefrom in said space, said tabs having slotted openings therebetween providing said pressure reducer.

35. A pressure gradient dosing system for a fluid supply system, comprising an additive delivery system having a fluid inlet and a fluid outlet, a flow passage including a portion extending from said inlet to said outlet, a first pressure zone along said flow passage communicating with said inlet, a second pressure zone along said flow passage communicating with outlet, said second pressure zone having a lower pressure than said first pressure zone, such that there is a pressure gradient between said first and second pressure zones, an additive reservoir responsive to said pressure gradient to release additive to said flow passage,
wherein:
fluid flows from upstream to downstream along said flow passage, including from said inlet to said outlet;
said flow passage has a pressure reducer therealong creating said pressure gradient;
said additive reservoir has first and second ports, said first port communicating with said first pressure zone, said second port communicating with said second pressure zone;
said additive delivery system has a mounting plate for mounting in said fluid supply system, said additive reservoir being spaced from said mounting plate by a space therebetween, said pressure reducer being in said space;
said pressure reducer comprises a venturi extending axially in said space and tapering radially outwardly as it extends axially toward said mounting plate.
